//types of tests it covers
UI E2E with POM + BDD, API smoke, accessibility a11y, reporting, and CI

healthcare-bdd-framework/
 ├─ src
 │   └─ test
 │       ├─ java
 │       │   ├─ pages
 │       │   │   └─ LoginPage.java
 │       │   ├─ stepDefinitions
 │       │   │   └─ LoginSteps.java
 │       │   └─ runners
 │       │       └─ TestRunner.java
 │       └─ resources
 │           └─ features
 │               └─ login.feature
 ├─ pom.xml
 ├─ testng.xml
 └─ README.md

 //what is inside
 Selenium + Java + TestNG + Cucumber (BDD)
 Page Object Model for CURA Healthcare demo site
 UI tests: login, book appointment
 API test: FDA drug event public API (RestAssured)
 Accessibility: axe-core scan example
 Reports: Cucumber HTML + ExtentReports
 CI: GitHub Actions workflow (headless Chrome) for push/PRs
 Config: config.properties (URL, headless, waits)

 //run locally
 mvn clean test -Dsurefire.suiteXmlFiles=testng.xml
 To see the browser: set headless=false in src/test/resources/config.properties.

 //run specific test types
 mvn clean test -Dcucumber.filter.tags="@ui"
 mvn clean test -Dcucumber.filter.tags="@api"
 mvn clean test -Dcucumber.filter.tags="@a11y"

 //add to your github
 Extract the ZIP.
 git init && git add . && git commit -m "Healthcare BDD framework"
  Create a repo on GitHub and push:

git branch -M main
 git remote add origin <your-repo-url>
 git push -u origin main